review_blob: Tons of pine and citrus aroma and flavor. Enjoying a 4-pack. I get punched in the nose with a piney aroma. The citrus (pineapple, mango) hops stand out with a nice balanced bitter finish.
beer_name: Fat Heads Hop JuJu Imperial IPA

review_blob: Incredible beer out of can. Smooth beer with piney notes, tropical fruit and nice subtle bitter finish.
Holy moly this is a smooth ipa. Just delicious hoppy smoothness that goes down so smooth.
Nice stout. Toffee, smoked vanilla, hint of coffee and nice boozey kick at the end. Let it warm a bit and the chocolate and that hint of coffee are mire apparent.
Appearance is dark brown red. Taste of molases, mix fruit and nice slight bitter finish. Reminds me of Averys The Reverand. Both good beers...
Aroma of chocolate and vanilla. Taste is excellent, hint of coffee, chocolate and vanilla. Very smooth and nice boozy finish.
Nice sour. Definitely taste the champagne yeast. Strawberries and honey are mixed in the finish. A lot going on here...
Aroma of boozy black licorice. Taste of fruity notes and chocolate malts. Nice bitter finish that lingers on the tongue...
beer_name: Evil Twin Christmas Eve at a New York City Hotel Room (2011-)

review_blob: Nice beer. Cherry aroma with dark brown pour. Taste is a nice, subtle fruity taste with the cherry standing out. The honey gives this a nice finish.
beer_name: Tregs The Mad Elf Holiday Ale

review_blob: Nice cream stout with smooth finish. Hint of coffee and cream malts. Appearance is a beautiful frothy dark brown.
Really enjoying this one. Smooth ale tatse with notes of vanilla and maple. Oak finish is subtle, but very nice.
Taste is cloves, pine and nutmeg. Minor bitterness on the tongue and finish of warm light cinnamon. Decent beer, but not my favorite dark horse.

Aroma has hint of coffee and booze. Very nice frothy head and lacing lays well. Taste has is a roasted malt flavor, light bitter booziness, slight chocolate and coffee flavor. Coffee flavor is light, but has a nice coffe grain taste on the finish.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Anubis Imperial Coffee Porter

review_blob: I really enjoyed this beer. Light ale that goes down smooth and had a slight bitter finish.

O was excited to try this and it was just OK. I did not get much of the cocoa nibs and the cheery flavor dominated the taste. More dark fruit malt and a reminder of cherry coke. Not a bad thing, just not what I expected...
Nice coffee stout. Aroma is ok, but appearance was excellent. The head was crazy and very active. Decent taste and an average coffee stout.
Very nice stout. Tatse is a nice semi-sweet matly oatmeal with a hint of chocolate. Nice bitter finish.
Pours medium brown, nice head and lacing. Slight bitter taste with notes of mango finish. Enjoyed the hop kick as well.
beer_name: North Coast Class of 88 Barley Wine

review_blob: Nice coffee aroma. Very nice coffee malty flavor with a nice oatmeal texture smooth finish. Slightly bitter end which is enjoyable.
Aroma of vanilla oak and espresso. Same with tatse. Sharp vanilla oak bits turns to espresso maltiness. Nice bitter warming finish with a lingering coffee flavor. Very delicious.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Espresso Oak Aged

review_blob: Light coffee flavor. Not the robust coffee, oatmeal or espresso as I expected. Good coffee malt flavor but a bit bland finish for me. I imagine on tap this would be much better.
Very good. Nice smooth tatse with cocoa, coffee, and vanilla notes. Love the cocoa and cofffee finish.
Solid 3.5. Good, not great. Not much aroma, tatse is malty, hint of chocolate and coffee. Bitter finish.
Very nice coffee aroma. Nice hazy brown color. Taste is a very malty and the coffee finish is nice and strong. This is a nice enjoyable fall beer.
Great oatmeal and chocolate aroma. Denotes creamy head flavor with chocolate and oat flavor.
Great chocolate ale. Loved the on tap and very good in bottle. So smooth and great chocolate aroma and taste!
Interesting beer. Oak aged amber with coffee. Started off just ok with more of a Smokey oak tatse. Really liked this as it warmed. Nice malty flavor and a hint of coffee.
Tasty coffee porter. Nice coffee aroma and taste. Hints of chocolate. Pretty Decent porter and I would get again.
Sweet stout that pours very nice and has nice cocoa malty taste. Really enjoyed the taste, but not as much flavor as I hoped.
Awesome beer. Definitely want to drink this at room temperature. Hint of vanilla, sweet bourbon and smooth finish.
Nice dark pour. Hint of molases in aroma. Powerful aroma of slight chocolate and licorice malts. Very good.
Nice dark rich stout. Definitely cream flavored, rich with a nice malted roast finish.
Jet black pour, nice coffee aroma. Tatse is very good. Smooth chocoolate notes and light coffee flavor.
2011 bottle. Pours dark brown. Carmal malt and chocolate notes. Very malty nice finish.
beer_name: Stone / The Alchemist / Ninkasi More Brown than Black IPA

review_blob: Excellent hop aroma and taste. Goes down smooth and nice balance. One of the most enjoyable beers readily available.
Not bad. One I had was bottled June 2012. Would be better fresh. Munich hops appear the strongest aroma wise. Might try the fresher one next time.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Rocket Dog Rye IPA

review_blob: Excellent aroma. So smooth. Taste is mango, fruity, and such a smooth finish. FFF continues to impress.
Wow this Tasmanian hops are very interesting. Aroma is the hops and is something that I have never smelled before. Taste is the pineapple and mango notes. Very glad to try this...
Very good. Strong tangerine flavor, very hoppy notes. Nice citra hops as well. I enjoyed this.
Dark horse is an awesome brewery. This beer has a nice mix of chocolate and coffee. Taste is light coffee, hints of chocolate and a nice malty mild- bitter finish.
beer_name: Dark Horse Reserve Special Black Ale

review_blob: Pours dark black. Aroma is of a light coffee. Taste is hint of chocolate and light coffee. Very good. Smooth finish.
Medioce beer. Light pale ale.. light ibu and 6% - you get what it is expected and as advertised.
beer_name: Triton Sin Bin Belgian Pale Ale

review_blob: From bottle. This is a very well balanced beer. Hops were subtle, bitterness mild and maltiness fair. Very drinkable and enjoyable.
Had on draft and big beer festival. Dark black appearance with nice stout and cream mix. Hint of bourbon is smooth and this beer is excellent. KBS was slightly better, but both are amazing beers.
Light and refreshing. Nice light hops. Very light brown appearance. Found this in the back on the fridge and enjoyed it!
Nice bitter hop and caramel malt taste. I would enjoy this more on a hit summer day. Good bitter taste and finish.
Great citra pale ale. Clean pour, excellent citra aroma. Tatse is citra smooth, great mango flavor. Excellent beer - just a notch below zombie dust!
Nice mild citra aroma. Pour is nice light golden amber. Poured from bottle. Light flavor, nice smooth finish. Good easy to drink beer.
beer_name: Three Floyds Pride & Joy Mild Ale

review_blob: Enjoyable beer. Clean pour, amber brown. Taste is very light and almost fruity. Not much aroma or lacing, but going down it is fairly smooth.
Holy shit this is amazing. Aroma of coffee, toffee, bourbon, vanilla bean. Taste is just amazing. Great coffee flavor, hint of bourbon and smooth.
